Manchester United chief Ed Woodward has backed Ole Gunnar Solskjaer to remain in charge of the club. The United manager retained the board’s support despite the Red Devils losing 2-0 at home to Burnley on Wednesday night, according to Sky Sports. United have made their worst league start to a campaign since the 1988-1989 season. Solskjaer has now lost 12 Premier League matches as the Red Devils’ permanent boss – more than he’s won. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The Norwegian could have seen the club move to within three points of fourth-placed Chelsea with a win over Burnley on Wednesday night. But, the 2-0 defeat was a major dent in their hopes of qualifying for next season’s Champions League.